to walk there. Even though you can walk for hours without really turning a corner from the main road, and still not arrive in our town, the groceries are only a ten-minute walk away when you stay in a riad.

The main road is really dusty, so when you get back from your walk, you have red dust from head to toe and all over the groceries. To load up the grocery store right outside our riad, we brought a large plastic container to put our produce directly into after loading most of it on our heads as we walked.

All the colorful spices,

A man walking his donkey,

And babies don't forget the babies.

After purchasing all the goods needed for the next day's home cooked meal, we bravely struck it out on our own to explore the dusty, dusty road.

The watermelon guy.

With the kind of heat this year, watermelons weren't selling well in Morocco, so it was hard to come to a stand that actually has watermelons, and harder stil find ones that aren't dry and basically intolerable.
